TAUCETI-VERDICT-027d99ee2a314c3b94f9b1ac
{
  "verdict": "request_changes",
  "summary": "Several exported declarations are stated above their natural level: local SLSC data is promoted to a global typeclass, one helper carries an unused global hypothesis, and `TubeData` has irrelevant endpoint parameters.",
  "findings": [
    {
      "file": "TauCeti/AlgebraicTopology/FundamentalGroupoid/SemilocallySimplyConnected.lean",
      "line": 235,
      "issue": "`exists_pathHomotopyTrivial_neighborhood` assumes `[SemilocallySimplyConnectedSpace X]`, but the natural hypothesis is the already-defined local predicate at `x`.",
      "fix": "Restate it as `SemilocallySimplyConnectedAt x → ∃ U, IsOpen U ∧ x ∈ U ∧ IsPathHomotopyTrivial U`, then derive the global-class version as a corollary if needed.",
      "evidence": "The declaration is `public theorem exists_pathHomotopyTrivial_neighborhood [SemilocallySimplyConnectedSpace X] (x : X)`, and its proof is exactly `semilocallySimplyConnectedSpace_iff_paths.mp ‹_› x`; `semilocallySimplyConnectedAt_iff_paths` gives the same result from the local assumption."
    },
    {
      "file": "TauCeti/AlgebraicTopology/FundamentalGroupoid/SemilocallySimplyConnected.lean",
      "line": 248,
      "issue": "`exists_pathConnected_slsc_neighborhood` is similarly under-generalized: it only needs SLSC at the single point `x`, plus local path-connectedness.",
      "fix": "Take `h : SemilocallySimplyConnectedAt x` as an explicit argument and use the localized `exists_pathHomotopyTrivial_neighborhood`; keep the typeclass version as a wrapper.",
      "evidence": "The proof obtains one SLSC neighborhood of `x` and then replaces it by `pathComponentIn V x`; no SLSC information away from `x` is used."
    },
    {
      "file": "TauCeti/AlgebraicTopology/FundamentalGroupoid/SemilocallySimplyConnected.lean",
      "line": 292,
      "issue": "`TubeData (X) (x y) (n)` is over-parameterized: the structure fields do not mention `x` or `y`, so identical tube data is indexed by irrelevant endpoints.",
      "fix": "Define `TubeData (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] (n : ℕ)` and pass endpoints only to consumers such as `PathInTube` or `TubeData.toSet`.",
      "evidence": "The structure header includes `(x y : X)`, while the fields are only `U`, `V`, openness/path-connectedness/SLSC properties, and subset relations between `V` and `U`."
    },
    {
      "file": "TauCeti/AlgebraicTopology/FundamentalGroupoid/BasedPath.lean",
      "line": 580,
      "issue": "`exists_refined_terminal_vertex` assumes `[SemilocallySimplyConnectedSpace X]`, but the statement and proof only use local path-connectedness and the bundled tube data.",
      "fix": "Remove the unused `[SemilocallySimplyConnectedSpace X]` assumption from this helper.",
      "evidence": "The proof forms `W := V_last ∩ U` and returns `pathComponentIn W (endpoint α)` using openness and path-connectedness; it never invokes the SLSC class or `T.U_slsc`."
    }
  ]
}
